{"id":38541,"date":"2022-12-25T20:51:36","date_gmt":"2022-12-25T16:51:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38541"},"modified":"2023-04-21T12:19:35","modified_gmt":"2023-04-21T08:19:35","slug":"iblees-snout","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/12\/25\/iblees-snout\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Satan: Shaytan withdraws when Allah is remembered"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Mu&#8217;adh ibn Jabal reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, <strong>&#8220;Verily, Satan has a snout like that of a dog positioned over the son of Adam, reminding him of his lusts and his pleasures, bringing him vain hopes and bringing his whisperings to incite doubt in his Lord. When the servant says, \u2018I seek refuge in Allah, the Seeing, the Knowing, from the cursed Satan, I seek refuge in Allah lest they be present with me, for Allah alone is the Seeing and the Knowing.\u2019 Then, Satan withdraws his snout from over his heart.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Zahr al-Firdaws 795<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Shawkani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0630\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062c\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0644\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0625\u0650\u0628\u0652\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0633\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u062e\u064f\u0631\u0652\u0637\u064f\u0648\u0645\u064c \u0643\u064e\u062e\u064f\u0631\u0637\u064f\u0648\u0645\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0628\u0650 \u0648\u0627\u0636\u0650\u